  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_4' aria-label=\" Jawala Real Estate Pvt Ltd & Anr. versus Haresh pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('4','2025','2025_6_193_201','2025INSC669'); ><font size='4'> <strong>JAWALA REAL ESTATE PVT LTD & ANR.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>HARESH </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 6 S.C.R. 193</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 669</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010001872025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, PRASANNA BHALACHANDRA VARALE</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The question arose as regards the determination of the amount due and payable by the respondent-buyer to the appellant-developer for the allotment of flat. Headnotes&dagger; Allotment &ndash; Allotment of flat &ndash; Determination of the amount due Allotment of flat by the appellant-developer to the respondent-buyer &ndash; Non-payment of the balance amount &ndash; Cancellation of the allotment by the developer &ndash; Thereagainst, complaint by the buyer &ndash; Despite order of the National Commission, the appellant created third-party<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 12-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> MISCELLANEOUS APPLICATION No. 2426/2018</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2025','2025_6_193_201','2025INSC669','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a hr